.SH "NAME"
git\-bump\-version \- Create versioned tags
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.sp
.nf
\fIgit bump\-version\fP [\-\-help | \-h] [\-\-major | \-M] [\-\-minor | \-n]
          [\-\-patch | \-p] [<version>]
.fi
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
This command shifts up the \fIUnreleased\fP section on \fIGHANGELOG.md\fP
so that a new section, named with the version passed by argument,
is created to keep the modifications that was unreleased.
.sp
It also changes version of the root cmake project if a \fICMakeLists.txt\fP
is found.
.sp
On success it also creates a tag to the version.
.sp
If some error occur during the version bumping the chages are
immediately reverted.
.sp
GHANGELOG.md will be automaticaly created if it doesn\(cqt exist.
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.sp
<version>
.RS 4
The version argument must follow the semantic versioning 2.0.0* spec
so that it obey to the following format
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
where \f(CRMAJOR\fP, \f(CRMINOR\fP and \f(CRPATCH\fP are decimal integer greater than or
equal to zero. No leading zero is allowed in any part.
.sp
[*] Currently this command does not support versions with prerelease
or buildmetadatas strings.
.RE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\f(CR\-h\fP, \f(CR\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Prints help information.
.RE
.sp
\f(CR\-M\fP, \f(CR\-\-major\fP
.RS 4
Tweaks version major number.
Ignored if \fBversion\fP argument is present.
.RE
.sp
\f(CR\-m\fP, \f(CR\-\-minor\fP
.RS 4
Tweaks version minor number.
Ignored if \fBversion\fP argument is present.
.RE
.sp
\f(CR\-p\fP, \f(CR\-\-patch\fP
.RS 4
Tweaks version patch number.
Ignored if \fBversion\fP argument is present.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Creates a tag 1.0.0 with changes described in \f(CRUnrelease\fP section
in \f(CRCHANGELOG.md\fP.
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ git bump\-version 1.0.0
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
